                    <marginalia_text>
                        Fabrilium, aliarumq[ue] machinationum rarissima exempla: ex intimis geometrarum, et architectorum artificijs. 
                        Nec dubium est, mirabilia fuisse, qua[e] Romani milites, ducesq[ue] tantoper&egrave; stupebant, et pa[e]n&egrave; perhorrescebant. 
                        Da Marcellum, quem nihil humanarum artium, operumve perterrefecit.
                    </marginalia_text>
                </position>
            </language>
            <translation>Unique examples of engineering and other machines, from the most inner works of geometrians and architects. 
                And there is no doubt that those which so amazed and almost terrified the Roman soldiers and leaders were extraordinary ones. 
                Except Marcellus, who was not frightened of any human crafts or works.
            </translation>
        </marginalia>
        
